Key Match Events: Derrick White and Jayson Tatum combined for 43 points, leading the Boston Celtics to a 109-86 win over the Houston Rockets.
White scored 23 points and made six 3-pointers.
Jayson Tatum scored 10 of his 20 points down the stretch of the first half.
Payton Pritchard and Jrue Holiday totaled six 3-pointers and contributed 20 and 14 points, respectively.
Jalen Green led the Rockets with 27 points while Alperen Sengun added 14 points and seven rebounds.
The Celtics shot 62.5 percent in the first quarter and made 7 of 12 3-pointers.
Boston led by as many as 28 points in the final period.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Houston Rockets were injury-depleted, missing Amen Thompson (suspension), Tari Eason (leg), and Jabari Smith Jr. (broken hand).
Smith is scheduled to undergo surgery and is expected to be sidelined for four to eight weeks.
